    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Silvane sacra semicluse fra<supplied reason="lost">xino</supplied> <lb n="2"/>et huius alti summe custos hor<supplied reason="lost">tuli</supplied> <lb n="3"/>tibi hasce grates dedicamus musicas <lb n="4"/>quod nos per arva <expan><abbr>perq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> montis <note>sic</note> Alpicos <lb n="5"/>tuique luci suaveolentis hospites <lb n="6"/>dum ius guberno <expan><abbr>remq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> fungor Caesarum <lb n="7"/>tuo favore prosperanti sospitas <lb n="8"/>tu me meosque reduces Romam sistito <lb n="9"/>daque Itala rura te colamus praeside <lb n="10"/>ego iam dicabo mil<expan><ex>l</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> magnas arbor<supplied reason="lost">es</supplied> <lb n="11"/><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> Pomponi Victoris <expan><abbr>proc</abbr><ex>uratoris</ex></expan> Augustor<supplied reason="lost">um</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Iambic trimeters almost pure, inspired by Catullus. Since Titus Pomponius Victor is mentioned as procurator also in an epigraph found in the Alpes Poeninae (AE 1898, 0098), it is probable that both inscriptions are datable to the period after the unification of the two provinces. (B): Grenier: Z. 4: montes; Z. 5: lucus; Z. 12: ex genio Asteri (line not mentioned in other editions).</p>
            </div>
